---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SeasonCountdown from '../components/SeasonCountdown.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Season Countdown — Days Until Spring, Summer, Autumn or Winter | Clockr"
	description="How long until the next season? Live astronomical season countdown to the spring equinox, summer solstice, autumn equinox or winter solstice."
	category="seasons"
>
	<div class="sc-page">
		<div class="sc-header">
			<div class="sc-eyebrow">
				<span class="sc-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				SEASONS
			</div>
			<h1 class="sc-title">
				<span class="sc-gradient">Season Countdown</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="sc-subtitle">Find out exactly how long until the next season</p>
		</div>

		<SeasonCountdown client:load />

		<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
		<section class="sc-how">
			<h2 class="sc-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="sc-how-card">
				<p>
					There are two common ways to define the seasons. Astronomical seasons
					are based on Earth's position relative to the Sun — they begin at the
					solstices and equinoxes, when day length reaches its extremes or when
					day and night are roughly equal. Meteorological seasons, used by most
					weather services, divide the year into neat three-month blocks: spring
					from 1 March, summer from 1 June, autumn from 1 September, and winter
					from 1 December. This countdown uses astronomical dates because they
					mark precise, observable moments in Earth's orbit.
				</p>
				<p>
					Solstices and equinoxes are not fixed calendar dates. They occur when
					the Sun crosses certain points in the sky — the equator for equinoxes,
					and the Tropic of Cancer or Capricorn for solstices. Clockr calculates
					these moments using standard astronomical formulas (based on Jean
					Meeus's <em>Astronomical Algorithms</em>), which account for Earth's
					elliptical orbit and the gravitational pull of the Moon and other
					planets. That is why the March equinox might fall on 19, 20, or 21
					March depending on the year, and why the exact time shifts by a few
					minutes each year.
				</p>
				<p>
					Seasons are reversed in the Southern Hemisphere. When the Northern
					Hemisphere experiences the June solstice and its longest day, the
					Southern Hemisphere has its shortest day and the start of astronomical
					winter. Likewise, the December solstice brings summer to the south and
					winter to the north. This page counts down to the astronomical season
					starts as observed from the Northern Hemisphere perspective, which is
					how most English-language references define spring, summer, autumn,
					and winter.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- FAQ -->
		<section class="sc-faq">
			<h2 class="sc-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="sc-faq-list">
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question">When does spring start?</summary>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Astronomical spring in the Northern Hemisphere begins at the March
							equinox (vernal equinox), when the Sun crosses the celestial
							equator heading north. This usually falls around 20 March, though
							the exact date and time vary slightly each year. Meteorological
							spring, used by weather forecasters, always starts on 1 March.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>What is the difference between astronomical and meteorological
						seasons?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Astronomical seasons begin at solstices and equinoxes — precise
							points in Earth's orbit around the Sun. Meteorological seasons use
							fixed calendar dates: 1 March (spring), 1 June (summer), 1
							September (autumn), and 1 December (winter). Weather services prefer
							meteorological seasons because they align with monthly climate
							records. Astronomical seasons match what you see in the sky: the
							longest and shortest days, and equal day and night.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question">When is the summer solstice?</summary>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							The summer solstice in the Northern Hemisphere occurs around 21
							June each year, when the North Pole is tilted closest to the Sun
							and the day is longest. The exact date and time shift by a few
							hours from year to year — select Summer above to see the precise
							countdown and UTC time for the next summer solstice.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question">When is the winter solstice?</summary>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							The winter solstice in the Northern Hemisphere falls around 21
							December, when the North Pole is tilted farthest from the Sun and
							the night is longest. Like other solstices and equinoxes, the
							exact moment varies slightly each year. Select Winter above for
							the live countdown to the next winter solstice.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>Why do the seasons start on different dates each year?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Astronomical season starts depend on Earth's exact position in its
							orbit, which is affected by the elliptical shape of the orbit,
							leap years, and gravitational interactions with the Moon and
							planets. A tropical year (the time between successive March
							equinoxes) is about 365.2422 days, not a whole number of calendar
							days, so equinox and solstice times drift within a one- or
							two-day window on the calendar.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question"
						>Are the seasons reversed in the Southern Hemisphere?</summary
					>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Yes. When it is summer in the Northern Hemisphere (around the June
							solstice), it is winter in the Southern Hemisphere, and vice versa
							at the December solstice. The March equinox marks the start of
							autumn in the south and spring in the north. This countdown follows
							the Northern Hemisphere convention used in most UK and US
							references.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- RELATED TOOLS -->
		<div class="sc-related">
			<h3 class="sc-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="sc-related-grid">
				<a href="/days-until-christmas" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Days Until Christmas</span></a
				>
				<a href="/year-progress" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Year Progress Bar</span></a
				>
				<a href="/days-until-halloween" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Days Until Halloween</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
	.sc-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.sc-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.sc-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-eyebrow-square {
		width: 8px;
		height: 8px;
		border-radius: 2px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		flex-shrink: 0;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: initial;
	}

	.sc-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.sc-tool {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.sc-hero-band {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		width: 100vw;
		margin-left: calc(50% - 50vw);
		padding: 48px 24px 56px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d1f17, #1a2e24);
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
		overflow: hidden;
		position: relative;
	}

	.sc-hero-decor {
		position: absolute;
		inset: 0;
		pointer-events: none;
		user-select: none;
	}

	.sc-float-emoji {
		position: absolute;
		display: inline-block;
		line-height: 1;
		transform: rotate(var(--rotation, 0deg));
		animation: sc-float 4s ease-in-out infinite;
		opacity: 0.9;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.sc-float-emoji {
			opacity: 0.35;
		}
	}

	@keyframes sc-float {
		0%,
		100% {
			transform: translateY(0) rotate(var(--rotation, 0deg));
		}
		33% {
			transform: translateY(-10px) rotate(calc(var(--rotation, 0deg) - 3deg));
		}
		66% {
			transform: translateY(-5px) rotate(calc(var(--rotation, 0deg) + 3deg));
		}
	}

	.sc-hero-centre {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		text-align: center;
		position: relative;
		z-index: 1;
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 720px;
	}

	.sc-season-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
		width: 100%;
		margin-bottom: 36px;
	}

	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.sc-season-grid {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		}
	}

	.sc-season-card {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		gap: 8px;
		padding: 20px 12px;
		background: rgba(12, 12, 12, 0.6);
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
		border-radius: 16px;
		cursor: pointer;
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			background 0.2s ease,
			box-shadow 0.2s ease;
		font-family: inherit;
		color: inherit;
	}

	.sc-season-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(116, 180, 155, 0.5);
		background: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.08);
	}

	.sc-season-card--active {
		border-color: rgba(116, 180, 155, 0.7);
		background: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		box-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.2);
	}

	.sc-season-emoji {
		font-size: 32px;
		line-height: 1;
	}

	.sc-season-label {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-countdown {
		display: flex;
		align-items: flex-end;
		justify-content: center;
		flex-wrap: wrap;
		gap: 8px 12px;
	}

	.sc-countdown-block {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.sc-countdown-num {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -2px;
		line-height: 1;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
		min-width: 64px;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.sc-countdown-num--days {
		font-size: clamp(80px, 13vw, 120px);
		letter-spacing: -4px;
		min-width: 100px;
	}

	.sc-countdown-sep {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 56px);
		font-weight: 900;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
		line-height: 1;
		margin-bottom: 26px;
		padding: 0 2px;
	}

	.sc-countdown-unit {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 2px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
	}

	.sc-target-date {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(15px, 2.5vw, 18px);
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
		margin: 28px 0 0;
		line-height: 1.5;
	}

	.sc-note {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 13px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
		line-height: 1.6;
		margin: 16px 0 0;
		max-width: 520px;
	}

	.sc-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.sc-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.sc-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.sc-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.sc-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.sc-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.sc-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.sc-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.sc-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-faq-item[open] .sc-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.sc-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.sc-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.sc-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.sc-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.sc-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.sc-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.4);
	}

	.sc-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.sc-title {
			font-size: 44px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		.sc-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}
</style>
